<td bgcolor="#CECECE" class="btext" width="100%"><b>Valve Get a Grip and GameGuard Step up</b> - <span class=bsmall>posted by  <a class='nNewsMailLink' href='mailto:StealthBuda@barrysworld.com'>StealthBuda</a> on Fri 26 October 2001 02:05:18 | <a href="comments.php?section=1&index=449" class=blink>Comments (0)</a></span></td>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" width=17><img src="images/item_icon.gif" width="17" height="17" alt="" border="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top>The <A HREF="http://www.catacombsnews.com/" target=_new>Catacombs</A> grabbed off the hlds mailing list this statement:<br><br><span class=quote>We're working now on our own anti-cheating technology now. It's our highest priority for the next Half-Life engine release.</span> Erik Johnson <br><br>They seam to think <span class=quote>that Valve has no plans to use PunkBuster as was previously indicated by a news post on the PunkBuster Site.</span><br><br>[ Taken from <A HREf="http://www.catacombsnews.com/" target=_new>the Catacombs</A> ]<br><br>Worth a look in the mean time is <A HREF="http://www.project-gameguard.org/pages/index.php?lang=en" target=_new>Project GameGuard</A> a punk buster styleee anti cheat system.<br><br><span class=quote>The result of our project should be a simple-to-use-tool for gamers protecting them from cheaters, rewarding their honest attitude toward gaming. <br>A tool to find and eliminate cheaters from our game servers!</span><br><br>I wish them all the best, cheaters beware, gg and valve are on yoru case.</td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
